
🧾 Project Description

Title: Infectious Disease Awareness Hub

Overview:
This website is designed to educate the public about infectious diseases, how they spread, prevention methods, and when to seek medical help. It targets students, families, and communities with accessible, easy-to-understand information.

Objectives:

Raise awareness about common infectious diseases (e.g., malaria, tuberculosis, COVID-19)
Promote preventive practices like hygiene, vaccination, and early testing
Provide reliable, simple health guidance
Combat misinformation with clear facts

Key Features:

Disease information pages
Prevention tips
Symptoms checker (basic interactive tool)
Latest health alerts/news section
Contact/help resources

Target Audience:

General public
Students
Community health workers
